<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>PK would be grand if not for the idiots</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Selyen">Selyen</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 1:13 a.m. 7/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> PK would be grand if not for the idiots<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>PK would be grand if not for the idiots. The PK system is a system that has the potential of promoting a self-regulating rpg society. It also has the greatest potential of raising an rpg to the highest pinacle of an rpg experience. But.....(you knew this was coming) the PK system, not unlike other well-thought systems, falls prey to the type of people that it attracts. I'm not saying that all PK'ers are bad people (most are cool i've found in my experience), but, as you know, it takes only one rotten apple to ruin a barrel of apples. For instance, the Communist government system would be an ideal system if not for all of the power-hungry and corrupt politicians (idiots and @$$holes) who wind up running the show. In other words, it's a system that relies on the intelligence and humility of all who participate. The same applies directly to pk. If all PK participants were the role-playing humble type and killed only for rp purposes, this system would be one to be beheld by all that played EQ. So i beg of you, if you're not intelligent and responsible enough to game in a PK environment and do it right, please don't get involved.

<P>l
<P>God bless all, and i'll see ya in final.
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
